article.headline: Navy 79, William & Mary 63
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Kaleo Kina topped off a strong overall performance with 18 points, and Navy beat William and Mary, 79-63, Tuesday night. Kina added seven rebounds, six assists and five steals to his season-high scoring. He also scored Navy's first nine points as the Midshipmen jumped to an 11-2 lead and never trailed. Navy extended its lead to 20-8 midway through the first half and the Tribe never got closer than nine points the rest of the way. The Midshipmen (5-2) are off to their best start since 1998-1999 when they began the season 6-1. Adam Trumbower and Adam Payton had 12 points each to lead William and Mary (1-3). The Tribe was without its top playmaker and second leading scorer, David Schnieder, who was injured. Greg Sprink added 15 points and Corey Johnson scored 10 for Navy, which shot 61.4 percent for the game and made 9 of 14 three-pointers. Navy led 38-28 at halftime and stretched its lead to 44-27 but the Tribe went on an 8-0 run to close the margin to 44-35 with 15 minutes left. William and Mary trailed 49-40 at 12:49, but a 21-6 run put Navy ahead 70-46 with 6:36 to play. William and Mary shot 40 percent, but made only 4 of 21 three-point tries.
